div.p:
“Among them, bodhisattvas understand that the inner sense sphere of the
                  eyes is subject to sickness, aging, and death; is empty of both ‘me’ and ‘mine’;
                  is ablaze with the fires of desire, aversion, and ignorance; is ablaze with birth,
                  aging, sickness, death, sorrow, lamentation, suffering, unhappiness, and despair;
                  and is ablaze with suffering.
